cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.SOC, cs.IR, cs.HC 

This paper focuses on the interplay of social and semantic components in social media systems, specifically Flickr and Last.fm. It explores the tagging activity of users and their explicit social network representation. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the sub-categories of Social and Information Retrieval (cs.SI), Social Networks and Graph Analysis (cs.SOC), and Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC). Additionally, the paper uses statistical models to analyze the data, which could place it in the sub-categories of Machine Learning (cs.LG) or Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS).
